{With 8 points, NORTH is not strong enough to open the bidding.

SOUTH has 13 points, barely meeting the minimum for a 1-opening. Note that the fifth and 
sixth \S each added 1 point to his count. He opens 1\S.

Although NORTH passed originally, she must respond to SOUTH's opening bid. Since she has 
three \Ss she raises to 2\S.

In light of NORTH's weak response SOUTH passes.}

